{
  "texts": [
    "To assess metacognition, we introduce MetaMedQA 24, an extension, and modification of the MedQA-USMLE benchmark 25, designed to evaluate LLMs' metacognition on medical problems.",
    "Our enhanced benchmark employs techniques such as confidence scoring and uncertainty quantification to assess not only the accuracy of LLMs but also their capacity for self-assessment and identification of knowledge gaps.",
    "This approach aims to provide a holistic evaluation framework that aligns more closely with the practical demands of clinical settings, ensuring that the deployment of LLMs in healthcare can be both safe and effective.",
    "Moreover, the implications of this research extend beyond healthcare, potentially informing the development and evaluation of AI systems in other high-stakes domains where selfawareness and accurate self-assessment are critical.",
    "In this work, we show that current LLMs demonstrate significant limitations in metacognitive abilities crucial for clinical decisionmaking."
  ]
}